HEADWORD: All-hail
<hw>All`-hail"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To salute; to greet.</def>
<mark>[Poet.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whiles I stood rapt in the wonder of it, came missives from the
king, who <qex>all-hailed</qex> me ⟦ldquo⟧Thane of Cawdor.⟦rdquo⟧</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Allhallond</ent>⟦br⟧
